title:Pulled Pork Sandwich
ingredients:For the sauce...//
1 large onion, chopped//
6 cloves garlic, peeled//
1 pickled jalape√±o pepper, seeded and chopped//
2 teaspoons chipotle chili powder//
1 tablespoon tomato paste//
2 tablespoons Dijon mustard//
3/4 cup distilled white vinegar//
1 teaspoon paprika//
1/3 cup ketchup//
2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce//
1/4 cup light brown sugar//
Salt//
For the pork...//
1 bay leaf//
3 pounds pork butt shoulder roast//
Hamburger buns
instructions:Puree each sauce ingredient in a blender until smooth.//
Put sauce, bay leaf, and pork into a large pot and add 1 quart of water.//
Bring mixture to boil, then reduce to simmer.//
Cook covered for 2 hours, turning frequently until meat pulls apart with fork.//
Remove from heat and cool pork in sauce.//
Remove from sauce and shred into small pieces.//
Put sauce back on the stove, and bring it to low boil.//
Let it boil till it has been reduced by two thirds.//
Add pork and salt to sauce.//
Remove bay leaf from sauce and serve the pork hot over hamburger buns.